<paragraph blockId="4.[151,939,1311,1372]" box="[151,287,1346,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,277,1346,1372]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 9–16" captionStart-1="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId-0="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetBox-1="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId-0="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetId-1="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9–19</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" box="[151,1131,1423,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,250,1423,1449]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Length:</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[325,431,1424,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
, 5.7 mm; male 
<typeStatus box="[611,715,1424,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">paratype</typeStatus>
, 5.4 mm; female 
<typeStatus box="[919,1023,1424,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">paratype</typeStatus>
, 6.4 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,388,1462,1488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[270,383,1462,1488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[479,605,1462,1488]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, well produced anteriorly, anterior margin rounded; crown with median length 2/3 interocular width and 2/5 transocular width; epicranial suture weakly visible, temporal and frontogenal sutures distinct. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[793,918,1540,1566]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with width approximately equal to transocular width. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[608,677,1578,1604]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with membrane distinct on apical portion, including apical cells and apex of anteapical cells.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[309,433,1656,1682]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) dark brown with numerous small yellow maculae. Crown with yellow line behind eyes. Face dark brown with yellow maculae on frons, genae, and antennal ledges. Venter dark brown. Legs pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,152,255]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[305,389,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with macrosetae on apical portion and extending anteriorly along ventral margin; apical portion with apicoventral inner process bearing numerous setae. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1391,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, narrowing gradually toward apex, with macrosetae near outer margin of ventral surface, and with some setae on dorsal surface. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[673,764,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly beyond apex of connective; with distinct median lobe on outer margin; portion beyond lobe curved; apex truncate. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[160,248,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, Y-shaped. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[714,802,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with shaft slightly curved ventrally; apical portion expanded with distinct dorsal lobe; median portion with laterodorsal expansion bearing small setae. Paraphyses (
<figureCitation box="[370,504,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, X-shaped; pair of rami directed anteriorly narrow, pair directed posteriorly broadened toward apex; stalk approximately as long as anterior rami. Anal tube (segment X), in ventral view, with pair of apical areas on ventral margin with setae similar to those of pygofer process.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" startId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" targetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" targetPageId="5">
