</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" startId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" targetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1170,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,348,1170,1194]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">FIGURES 17–19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[355,616,1171,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Exogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomaculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[355,616,1171,1194]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Exogonia flavomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[621,697,1172,1193]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[621,697,1172,1193]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1281,1887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,741,1281,1307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
Female genitalia (based on 
<specimenCount box="[553,727,1281,1307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">one paratype</specimenCount>
).
</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[913,1002,1281,1307]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) broader than long; lateral margins approximately rectilinear; posterior margin with distinct concavity medially; surface with small setae, mostly on posterior portion, and very few longitudinal striae on median portion. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1234,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with posterior margin narrowly rounded; macrosetae on posterior portion, extending anteriorly along ventral margin. Second valvulae (
<figureCitation box="[478,571,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, moderately expanded beyond basal curvature; shaft narrowing slightly toward subacute apex; preapical prominence small but distinct; teeth extending from expanded basal portion to apical portion, basal teeth large and rectangular, followed by gradually smaller ones; teeth and dorsal and ventral margins of anteapical portion of shaft bearing denticles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1281,1887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,1032,1590,1616]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
Intraspecific variation (based on all male and female 
<typeStatus box="[894,1024,1590,1616]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">paratypes</typeStatus>
)
</emphasis>
. Crown sometimes with anterior margin narrowly rounded and epicranial, temporal, and frontogenal sutures very distinct. Female 
<typeStatus box="[1333,1436,1629,1655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">paratype</typeStatus>
with median length of crown 1/2 transocular width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
